description:
&lt;p&gt;Whittington Health Trust are looking for a Band 6 Specialist Speech and Language therapist to join their team. The post is based within the multidisciplinary community therapy team providing community therapeutic rehabilitation to residents living in Islington.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The main duties of the post are but not limited to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Providing speech and language therapy input to adults referred to the department&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Offering specialist input in the assessment rehabilitation and management of adults in the community setting with complex communication and swallowing difficulties, including knowledge of AAC and LSVT&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensuring that specialist clinical and professional standards of practice are maintained&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Offer regular clinical support to junior staff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Essential Requirements for the role:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;BCS Speech Path or Equivalent&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;HCPC Registration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;6 months NHS experience in a similar role  &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
